<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>tailoring. . .</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?WyrmRydeR">WyrmRydeR</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:08 a.m. 29/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> tailoring. . .<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/tunare.cgi?read=33" TARGET=_self>tailoring and smithing</A> (Nenan newbie Wizard)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> how do i use tailoring and blacksmithing?

<BR>&gt; thx for any help
<P>To Tailor you need a large or small sewing kit and then you need to place your ruined and pattern (for patchwork armor anyway) then hit combine and see if it works. I am at a Tailor skill of about 30 and can make patchwork fairly consistently, 8 out of 10 times, at lest. The size of the armor is dependent on the type of pelt (all must be ruined for patchwork) Large-bear, Medium-cat, Small-Wolf. There is a lot more info I could give e-mail me (wyrmrydereq@usa.net) and/or check out eqvault.com 's trade area. Also, I urge you to look into affiliating yourself with the Tunare Trade Coalition, if you plan on selling your wares to others. by the way, if anyone knows of a smith making studs or boning please let me know they are required ot make studded and banded armor, respectively.
<P>Rindara the Lost
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
